commit.message: Fix tests with optional packages (lxml and xmlschema)
Fix test for fn:default-collation() on Windows platform
Update release v2.0.0 info
Augment tests coverage

Fix descendant short // and nodes iteration

  - Fix etree_iter_nodes()
  - Add child_axis property to XPathToken
Fix op:union (admits XPath nodes only)
Fix fn:round(), fn:sum() and fn:subsequence()

Refactor arguments related to variables

  - Parser's variables renamed to variable_types
  - Context's variable_values renamed to variables
  - Remove get_sequence_type(). If a variable's type is missing
    the sequence type is 'item()' or 'item()*'
  - Add instance check for xs:anySimpleType in is_instance()
Refine select_xsd_nodes() in XPathToken

Change add_xsd_type() and fix comparison operators

  - add_xsd_type() is now focused on item (attribute or element). The
    new version is less flexible but covers all node container types.
Add cast_to_qname() and other helpers for QNames

Add cast_to_double() to XPathToken

  - Common method for basic type promotions (untyped)
  - Clean costructors and remove cast_to_number()

Split XSD 1.0 and XSD 1.1 builtins

  - Two distinct dict for builtin types lookup
  - Add DoubleProxy10 and Float10 for XSD 1.0 type cast
Incorporate check_comparison_operands() into comparison operators
Fix 'cast as' errors for XSD datatypes

Transform get_comparison_data() to generator functions

  - Fix W3C general comparison tests
  - With generator ~17% faster on running W3C tests!

Fix for fn:replace(), fn:matches() and fn:string-join()

  - Replace empty sequence error in token's get_argument()
    with a type error XPTY0004

Clean package imports and doc API

  - Pratt API removed from base package (off topic)

Clean datatypes class hierarchy

  - Leave only AtomicTypeABCMeta metaclass
  - Mix derived classes (AnyURI, QName, Float, Duration) and virtual
    derived classes of AnyAtomicType.

Fix EBV for schema-typed nodes

  - Fix split_expanded_name() (use groups() instead of groupdict())

Closing W3C tests resolution for release

  - About ~300 W3C tests failing and ~100 tests skipped/unknown
  - Revert on preferring the usage of None instead of [] for
    evaluation (simplify Python code and it's lighter)

Fix fn:name(), fn:local-name() and other functions

  - Fix / for schema context

Fix fn:in-scope-prefixes(), fn:idref() and again fn:id()

  - TODO: DTD parsing for ID and IDREF declaration

Replace match_xsd_type() with select_xsd_nodes() in XPathToken

  - The new method is a selector and works also with schemas
  - Add AbstractXsdSchema iterface
  - Improved schema path selection traversing wildcards
Fix fn:id() and fn:element-with-id()

Fix fn:document-uri()

  - Add also a search in context.documents for a matching
    document after the check of the attribute xml:base

Fix fn:collection()

  - add Collection to W3C test script: parse collection info
  - collection stability: TODO for a future release
Fix fn:min() and fn:max()
Fix fn:round-half-to-even()

Fix fn:distinct-values()

  - Have to use math.isclose() to check float against decimal
